Examples of using preparers with the [PerformOcr operation](../primitives#summarize-text) in AI Accelerator.

## Model creation (required)

This step is required for primitive single execution and for preparer bulk execution.

```sql
-- Create the model. It must support the perform_ocr operation.
SELECT aidb.create_model(
    'my_paddle_ocr_model',
    'nim_paddle_ocr',
    credentials => '{"api_key": "__NVIDIA_NIM_API_KEY__" }'::JSONB
);
```

## Primitive

```sql
-- Keyword arguments
SELECT * FROM aidb.perform_ocr(
    input => decode('', 'base64'),
    options => '{"model": "my_paddle_ocr_model"}'
);

-- Positional arguments
SELECT * FROM aidb.perform_ocr(
    decode('', 'base64'),
    '{"model": "my_paddle_ocr_model"}'
);
```

## Preparer with table data source

```sql
-- Create source test table
CREATE TABLE source_table__1527
(
    id      INT GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,
    content BYTEA NOT NULL
);
INSERT INTO source_table__1527
VALUES (1, decode('', 'base64'));

SELECT aidb.create_table_preparer(
    name => 'preparer__1527',
    operation => 'PerformOcr',
    source_table => 'source_table__1527',
    source_data_column => 'content',
    destination_table => 'ocr_data__1527',
    destination_data_column => 'parsed__text',
    source_key_column => 'id',
    destination_key_column => 'id',
    options => '{"model": "model__1527"}'::JSONB  -- Configuration for the PerformOcr operation
);

SELECT aidb.bulk_data_preparation('preparer__1527');

SELECT * FROM ocr_data__1527;
```

## Model compatibility

The AI accelerator data preparation pipeline validates the options at creation time, including the model compatibility with the OCR adapter. These errors are returned in that case:

```sql
-- This model does not support the OCR adapter
SELECT aidb.create_model('bert_model', 'bert_local');
```

```sql
-- Single execution fails
SELECT * FROM aidb.perform_ocr(
    input => decode('', 'base64'),
    options => '{"model": "bert_model"}'
);
__OUTPUT__
ERROR:  The requested adapter is not supported by the model provider: bert_local
```

```sql
-- Preparer creation fails
SELECT aidb.create_table_preparer(
    name => 'preparer__1527',
    operation => 'PerformOcr',
    source_table => 'source_table__1527',
    source_data_column => 'content',
    destination_table => 'ocr_data__1527',
    destination_data_column => 'parsed__text',
    source_key_column => 'id',
    destination_key_column => 'id',
    options => '{"model": "bert_model"}'::JSONB  -- Incompatible model
);
__OUTPUT__
ERROR:  Failed to create preparer: The requested adapter is not supported by the model provider: bert_local
```
